      "content": "i see. so you're saying the doctrine itself is fine, it was just the application that was wrong? some legal scholars argue that the whole idea of \"substantive\" due process is actually just a way for judges to inject their own personal political values into the law instead of just following the text. how would you explain that perspective to my students?",
